{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YFWgkAQveRy2KLQSE5KDe8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Hshsz6v5gYHfTEke2Ukybi","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n spark-pi create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'FINDINGS'\n=======================================================\nSPARK-PI NAMESPACE — COMPLIANCE AUDIT REPORT\nAudited: 2026-06-16\nAuditor: automated read-only inspection\n=======================================================\n\nSCOPE\n-----\nNamespace: spark-pi\nResources inspected: Roles, RoleBindings, ServiceAccounts, Deployments\n(spark-master, spark-worker), Job (spark-pi), Pods, ConfigMaps,\nNetworkPolicies.\n\n=======================================================\nSECTION 1 — COMPLIANT / CORRECTLY CONFIGURED\n=======================================================\n\n[PASS] SA-1  Dedicated ServiceAccount\n  A dedicated 'spark-pi' ServiceAccount exists. Neither the deployments nor\n  the job use the 'default' ServiceAccount, limiting credential blast radius.\n\n[PASS] SA-2  Namespaced Role (not ClusterRole)\n  'spark-pi-role' is a Role scoped to the spark-pi namespace, not a\n  ClusterRole. Permissions cannot be used cluster-wide.\n\n[PASS] SA-3  RoleBinding links SA to Role correctly\n  'spark-pi-role-binding' binds 'spark-pi-role' to the 'spark-pi'\n  ServiceAccount only; no wildcard subjects.\n\n[PASS] SA-4  RBAC resources are scoped\n  The Role grants access only to: services, configmaps,\n  persistentvolumeclaims, pods — no Secrets, no cluster-level resources.\n\n[PASS] IMG-1  Pinned image tag on all containers\n  All three workloads (spark-master, spark-worker, spark-submit job) use\n  'apache/spark:3.5.3' — a pinned digest-resolvable tag, not 'latest'.\n  This prevents silent image drift.\n\n[PASS] RES-1  CPU and memory requests+limits set on all containers\n  spark-master: requests cpu=200m/mem=512Mi, limits cpu=500m/mem=1Gi\n  spark-worker:  same as above\n  spark-pi job:  same as above\n  No container runs without resource governance.\n\n[PASS] JOB-1  Job backoffLimit=0\n  The spark-pi Job specifies backoffLimit=0, preventing runaway pod\n  restart loops on failure.\n\n[PASS] JOB-2  Job restartPolicy=Never\n  The job pod template uses restartPolicy=Never, consistent with\n  backoffLimit=0 and safe for a batch driver.\n\n[PASS] JOB-3  Job completed successfully\n  spark-pi job status: Complete (1 succeeded pod, 0 failures).\n  Completion observed at 2026-06-16T23:39:51Z.\n\n=======================================================\nSECTION 2 — GAPS / NON-COMPLIANT FINDINGS\n=======================================================\n\n[FAIL] SEC-1  [HIGH] No securityContext on any pod or container\n  All three pod specs (spark-master, spark-worker, spark-pi job) have\n  securityContext: {} at both pod and container level. The following\n  hardening fields are absent:\n    - runAsNonRoot: true           (containers may run as UID 0)\n    - runAsUser: <non-root UID>    (no explicit non-root UID enforced)\n    - allowPrivilegeEscalation: false  (privilege escalation not blocked)\n    - readOnlyRootFilesystem: true (root filesystem is writable)\n    - capabilities.drop: [ALL]     (Linux capabilities not dropped)\n  Risk: containers running as root with full capabilities. A container\n  escape grants root on the node.\n\n[FAIL] NET-1  [HIGH] No NetworkPolicy defined\n  kubectl get networkpolicy -n spark-pi returns no resources.\n  All pods in spark-pi have unrestricted ingress and egress — they can\n  reach any pod or service in the cluster and accept connections from any\n  source. Required policies:\n    - Ingress: allow only intra-namespace traffic (master <-> worker)\n      and external access to the Spark Web UI (port 8080) if needed.\n    - Egress: restrict to kube-dns (UDP/TCP 53), the Kubernetes API\n      server, and intra-namespace peers.\n\n[FAIL] RBAC-1  [MEDIUM] Role grants delete/update/patch on pods\n  'spark-pi-role' allows verbs [create, get, list, watch, delete, update,\n  patch] on pods. Spark executors only require create/delete of their own\n  pods. Granting update and patch on pods across the namespace is broader\n  than minimum necessary and enables modification of other pods' specs.\n\n[FAIL] IMG-2  [MEDIUM] imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent on all containers\n  All containers use imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent. If the image is\n  already present on a node (possibly a stale or tampered cached layer),\n  it will not be re-pulled, bypassing registry security scanning and\n  digest verification. Policy 'Always' is preferred in compliance-sensitive\n  environments to ensure each pod start verifies the registry digest.\n\n[FAIL] NS-1   [LOW] No LimitRange on namespace\n  No LimitRange exists in spark-pi. Any pod or container admitted without\n  explicit resource specs would run unconstrained. Current workloads all\n  set resources explicitly, but future workloads or ephemeral debug pods\n  would not be protected.\n\n[FAIL] NS-2   [LOW] No ResourceQuota on namespace\n  No ResourceQuota is set. There is no ceiling on the total CPU, memory,\n  or object count for the namespace, enabling a single namespace to\n  consume unbounded cluster resources.\n\n=======================================================\nSECTION 3 — SUMMARY TABLE\n=======================================================\n\nControl                          Status   Severity\n-----------                      ------   --------\nDedicated ServiceAccount         PASS     —\nNamespaced Role (not Cluster)    PASS     —\nRoleBinding scoped correctly     PASS     —\nRBAC resources scoped            PASS     —\nPinned image tag                 PASS     —\nCPU/memory limits on all pods    PASS     —\nJob backoffLimit=0               PASS     —\nJob restartPolicy=Never          PASS     —\nJob completed successfully       PASS     —\nPod/container securityContext    FAIL     HIGH\nNetworkPolicy present            FAIL     HIGH\nRole verbs least-privilege       FAIL     MEDIUM\nimagePullPolicy=Always           FAIL     MEDIUM\nLimitRange on namespace          FAIL     LOW\nResourceQuota on namespace       FAIL     LOW\n\nTotal: 9 PASS, 6 FAIL (2 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM, 2 LOW)\n\n=======================================================\nNEXT STEPS (for remediation planning — not applied here)\n=======================================================\n1. Add securityContext to all pod/container specs (runAsNonRoot,\n   allowPrivilegeEscalation: false, capabilities.drop: ALL,\n   readOnlyRootFilesystem where feasible).\n2. Apply NetworkPolicy resources restricting ingress/egress per workload.\n3. Narrow spark-pi-role: remove 'update' and 'patch' from pods verbs.\n4. Set imagePullPolicy: Always on all containers.\n5. Add LimitRange and ResourceQuota to the spark-pi namespace.\n\nNOTE: No changes were made to the cluster during this audit.\nFINDINGS\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with compliance findings in spark-pi namespace"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1840,"cache_read_input_tokens":33373,"output_tokens":3131,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1840,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":3131,"cache_read_input_tokens":33373,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1840,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1840},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":{"applied_edits":[]}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2390082e-90d1-47e7-a72e-a1fbb0b75b27","uuid":"9fa9c439-45a4-4b7f-a989-000000000002","request_id":"req_011Cc7psdbX6SpS5D7dBgGNP"}
